article.headline: Ehlinger injured, but No. 9 Texas survives Baylor 23-17
article.description: Shane Buechele came on for injured quarterback Sam Ehlinger early in the first quarter and No. 9 Texas slugged out a 23-17 win over Baylor that ended when the Bears' final pass sailed through the back of the end zone Saturday.
article.linkText: Ehlinger injured, but No. 9 Texas survives Baylor 23-17

images.name: Buechele shows beautiful touch on 44-yard TD pass
images.caption: Backup quarterback Shane Buechele lofts a perfect sideline throw to Collin Johnson, who extends and reels in a 44-yard Texas touchdown.

video.headline: Buechele shows beautiful touch on 44-yard TD pass
video.caption: Backup quarterback Shane Buechele lofts a perfect sideline throw to Collin Johnson, who extends and reels in a 44-yard Texas touchdown.
video.title: Buechele shows beautiful touch on 44-yard TD pass
video.description: Backup quarterback Shane Buechele lofts a perfect sideline throw to Collin Johnson, who extends and reels in a 44-yard Texas touchdown.

article.story: AUSTIN, Texas -- Shane Buechele came on for injured quarterback Sam Ehlinger early in the first quarter and No. 9 Texas beat Baylor 23-17 when the Bears' final pass sailed through the back of the end zone Saturday. Baylor quarterback Charlie Brewer drove the Bears from their own 3 to the Texas 17 before he had to rush his final three throws under intense pressure. The victory makes Texas (6-1, 4-0 Big 12 Conference) bowl eligible. Texas Freshman running back Keaontay Ingram ran for 110 yards, the Longhorns' first 100-yard rushing effort of the season. Defensive end Charles Omenihu had two sacks and was chasing Brewer on the last three plays. "We knew this wasn't going to be easy and obviously when your starting QB goes out on the first drive, there could have been some panic, a little shock," Texas coach Tom Herman said. Buechele finished Texas' opening drive after game officials made Ehlinger leave because his right, throwing hand was bleeding. Ehlinger went to the sideline and then the locker room before school officials announced he had injured his throwing shoulder. He returned to the sideline but didn't play again and changed into street clothes. After the game, Herman said Ehlinger has a shoulder sprain and would have an MRI to see if there is any ligament damage, but he hoped to have him throwing again in a few days. Buechele was the full-time starter in 2016, when he set several school freshman passing records, but he hadn't played yet this season. The Longhorns struggled to find any offensive rhythm for most of the game as Buechele passed for 184 yards with one touchdown and one interception. Texas is bowl eligible in mid-October for the first time since 2009, the last year the Longhorns won the Big 12 and played for a national championship. Texas had consecutive losing seasons from 2014-16 and didn't get to the postseason in 2015 and 2016. The Longhorns have now qualified for bowl games in both of Herman's seasons. Brewer passed for 245 yards and a touchdown for the Bears (4-3, 2-2), who were just 1-11 last season. "We are getting better and we're getting tougher and we're starting to figure this out," Baylor coach Matt Rhule said. "I told them it's OK this hurts, this should hurt, for the first time since I've been here I've saw tears in their eyes and I saw the older guys really hurting." THE TAKEAWAY Baylor: The Bears couldn't protect Brewer late. They ended their last three drives with Brewer either sacked or on the run as the pocket collapsed around him. The Bears' defense, the worst against the run in the Big 12, had a solid game after giving up 300 yards on the ground a week earlier. Texas: The Longhorns may be on edge waiting to see how serious Ehlinger's injury is and if next week's open date will give him time to recover before the next game. Ehlinger accounted for five touchdowns in a breakout victory over Oklahoma. He hasn't thrown an interception in 168 attempts, a school record. He also had played every snap this season until getting hurt. UP NEXT Baylor is off next week before visiting No. 6 West Virginia on Oct. 25. Texas is off next week before visiting Oklahoma State on Oct. 27. --- For more AP college football coverage: https://apnews.com/tag/Collegefootball and https://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- Follow Jim Vertuno at https://twitter.com/jimvertuno

videos.headline: Texas secures win over Baylor on last-second defensive stop
videos.description: With one second remaining, down six points at the Texas 17 yard line, Baylor's Charlie Brewer is leveled on his pass to the end zone that sails out of bounds, giving Texas a 23-17 victory.

videos.headline: Ehlinger exits game in 1st quarter
videos.description: Texas quarterback Sam Ehlinger heads to the locker room in the first quarter with an apparent cut on his right throwing hand.

videos.headline: Baylor QB delivers strike for 19-yard TD
videos.description: Baylor quarterback Charlie Brewer pumps and fires a 19-yard touchdown to Denzel Mims on their opening drive to take a 7-3 lead over Texas.

videos.headline: Texas legend Ricky Williams tries to pump up home crowd
videos.description: 1998 Heisman winner and Texas Longhorns' legend Ricky Williams shares a moment with the fans as he hoists his trophy at Darrell K Royal - Texas Memorial Stadium.

videos.headline: Longhorns-Bears get chippy in Texas
videos.description: Baylor wide receiver Jalen Hurd snuffs Texas linebacker Gary Johnson on the face mask as unsportsmanlike conduct penalties are called in the second quarter.

videos.headline: Humphrey plunges in wildcat TD
videos.description: Texas wide receiver Lil'Jordan Humphrey lines up under center in the wildcat formation and weaves into the end zone for a 3-yard touchdown run.

videos.headline: Texas DB swoops and snags interception
videos.description: Texas defensive back Caden Sterns gets a great read on Charlie Brewer's sideline throw and makes an incredible interception before halftime, his fourth of the season.

videos.headline: Buechele airmails interception
videos.description: Shane Buechele's deep ball is overthrown and lands in the hands of Baylor cornerback Raleigh Texada near midfield.

videos.headline: Hurd slides into end zone for 2-yard punch in
videos.description: Baylor wide receiver Jalen Hurd's number is called on a 3rd-and-goal as he dives into the end zone for a 2-yard touchdown, cutting Texas' lead down to 23-17.

videos.headline: Baylor DE carted off field with arm injury
videos.description: Baylor defensive end Deonte Williams collides with a teammate attempting to tackle Shane Buechele. Williams is carted off the field with an aircast around his right arm.
